# .dockerignore — exclusions for the API image build (Phase 3 Task 14).
#
# Two goals:
# 1. Keep the build context small. Docker tars the context and uploads it
#    to the daemon every build; node_modules alone is ~500 MB and would
#    dominate transfer time. Excluding it forces the Dockerfile to run
#    `npm ci` inside the image (which is what we want — reproducible).
# 2. Prevent secrets from leaking into the image. .env files contain
#    JWT_SECRET, DATABASE_URL etc. and MUST NOT ship in any layer. Even
#    if a later layer "deletes" them, the previous layer keeps them
#    forever in image history.

# ─── Local dependencies and build outputs ──────────────────────────────────
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
build
.vite
.cache

# ─── Secrets and local environment overrides ───────────────────────────────
# .env (any depth, any suffix) — server runtime env arrives via compose
# env_file / K8s Secret + ConfigMap, NEVER via a baked-in .env layer.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*

# ─── Git and version control ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Smaller context + we never want commit metadata in a runtime image.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# ─── IDE and OS detritus ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# ─── Local-only documentation and AI artefacts (per CLAUDE.md commit rules) ─
# These are gitignored AND must not leak into a Docker image either —
# the project bar treats them as production-equivalent secrets because
# they contain architectural reasoning competitors could harvest.
CLAUDE.md
docs_foundation
docs/superpowers
.claude
.mcp.json
Plan_ORG
*.pkl
feastbox-source-dump.txt
memory

# ─── Test files (skip in the production image) ──────────────────────────────
# Tests run on host via `npm --prefix server run test`, not in the runtime
# image. Excluding them shaves a few MB and reduces the attack surface
# (test fixtures sometimes hold credentials).
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.js
**/test-utils
**/__tests__
coverage
.nyc_output
vitest.config.js

# ─── Frontend source (this Dockerfile builds the API only) ──────────────────
# The Vue SPA is served by Vite locally during the demo, not by Express.
# Excluding /src and frontend tooling keeps the image focused.
src
public
index.html
vite.config.js
postcss.config.js
tailwind.config.js
# Root-anchored so only the repo-root manifests are excluded.
# server/package.json and server/package-lock.json are NOT matched and
# remain available for `COPY server/package.json ...` in the Dockerfile.
./package.json
./package-lock.json

# ─── Compose and infra manifests (don't need them inside the image) ─────────
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
k8s
